				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eskobar" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1173523); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1173523&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250847" alt="Eskobar" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1173523)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eskobar" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1173523); return false;" >Eskobar</a></span> <span class="odate time_1327867681 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Jan 2012 20:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1360976">
									

<p>Just to be clear: The University is not the center of its universe, any more than the Foundation is the center of ours. 98% of the University isn't anomalous in any way (to itself, at least). The physics department (Natural Philosophy) of the University is just the reason why we know that world exists, due to <a href="/hephaestus">experiments taking place</a> in the Natural Philosophy department.</p>
<p>Sort of like the maxim about how events that are mentioned in newspapers seem far more important in hindsight than they actually were at the time, just because that article suddenly becomes most of what we know of the world it describes.</p>

							</div>

								
